// Print Filled Diamond 5 (#0813)

// No input. Prints a 5-row filled diamond of `*` centered in a 5-col field: rows ` * `, `***`, `*****` (truncated to 5-col), `***`, ` * ` — actually use rows widths 1,3,5,3,1 centered on width-5 grid with leading spaces.

main

def main {
    stl.startup
    stl.output "  *\n ***\n*****\n ***\n  *\n"
    stl.loop
}
